    <text id="B1176T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How submits a requisition for flags, justifying its necessity by pointing to the
                    "impatience of the people to witness these emblems of restored authority."</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen &amp; <abbr expan="Abandoned">A.</abbr>
                    Lands<lb/>Sixth District <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> O. Brown, <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Assist Comr</abbr><lb/>Richmond <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-04-12">April 12th 1866</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to forward the enclosed Special Requisition with the request
                    that the Flags may be immediately furnished in order to prevent the impatience
                    of the people to witness these emblems of restored authority from breaking out
                    in demonstration against the Bureau Officers <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> of their freedom
                    to exhibit the Good and glorious insignia of our National Freedom and Power.</p>

                <p>The quotation in the Special Requisition setting forth the necessity is from the
                    President's Proclamation dated Washington DC April 2d 1866.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Colonel<lb/>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your Obedient Servant</salute>
                    <signed>W. Storer How<lb/><abbr expan="Brevet Major">Bt Maj</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Assistant Quartermaster">AQM</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
